Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the Intermediate FullStack Developer position with Winsupply. I bring over three years of professional experience in full-stack development, microservices architecture, and cloud-native systems, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade systems that directly reflect the technical depth and leadership responsibilities this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I architected a microservices-based AI layer that translates natural-language intents into validated RESTful API calls across 1,000+ endpoints — requiring rigorous service-oriented architecture design, multi-tier application patterns, and safe execution across distributed systems. I designed highly available and fault-tolerant code generation solutions using Object-Oriented Programming and design patterns to accelerate developer integration with platform RESTful APIs. To keep these systems production-ready, I built a comprehensive observability layer using Langfuse and LangSmith, covering distributed tracing, structured logging, and evaluation hooks. I led performance optimization efforts implementing multi-threaded orchestration with LangChain and LangGraph, reducing end-to-end latency by 60% and API costs by 50% through concurrency tuning — demonstrating the kind of technical excellence and continuous improvement mindset this role values. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I contributed to enterprise-scale infrastructure that thousands of users rely on daily. I designed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service using Python, PostgreSQL, and Redis with RESTful architecture, seamlessly handling file operations across AWS S3, Google Cloud Storage, and MinIO — giving me direct experience with multi-cloud backend design and integration. I also contributed to an Identity & Access Management platform built with React, Spring Boot, and AWS, supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications with multi-tier design and security best practices. I developed distributed workflows using AWS Step Functions and Lambda for long-running data imports, implementing fault-tolerant patterns to prevent timeouts — both of which required the systems-level thinking and operational stability focus this role demands. Together, these roles have prepared me to lead assigned development and integration projects from inception to delivery, collaborate effectively with business users to define requirements, and contribute meaningfully to Winsupply's core engineering responsibilities.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in technical communication, mentorship, and collaborative engineering — skills that translate directly into the mentorship and knowledge-sharing responsibilities central to this role. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I conducted applied research on StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion using PyTorch and LoRA on Pace University's HPC cluster, managing the full development lifecycle from training to deployment with CI/CD automation. I implemented secure model inference using vLLM and Hugging Face, ensuring fault-tolerant serving with performance monitoring. Beyond building the systems myself, I mentored 50+ students through hands-on workshops on GPU programming and building AI Agents. Designing and delivering those sessions required me to break down complex technical concepts clearly and accessibly — directly mirroring the mentorship and guidance responsibilities this role expects. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who builds with rigor, communicates with clarity, and champions engineering best practices across the team.

I have always been passionate about entrepreneurship and enabling others to achieve their dreams through technology, and I envision myself contributing my talent to furthering Winsupply's mission of helping capable, hard-working people achieve their dreams through wholesale distribution. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

